  "description": "<p>分类: <a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/category/transportation/\" rel=\"tag\">交通相关</a></p><div style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/06/volvos-self-driving-cars-hit-the-road\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://o.aolcdn.com/hss/storage/midas/bf5f922d3e1c701d30ae31049cfbf894/200093643/volvo-self-driving-2014-05-06-01.jpg\" /></a></div>\n<br />\n在<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/SelfDrivingCar/\">自动驾驶车辆</a>的这块领域，<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/tag/Volvo/\">Volvo</a> 现在也已经跟上了 <a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/04/28/google-self-driving-car-object-recognition-danger-update/\">Google</a> 与<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2012/04/20/cadillac-super-cruise/\">其它车厂</a>的进度，准备在瑞典哥特堡开始公开路测。这项名为\"Drive Me\"计划的首个阶段，会先暂时将自动驾驶车在预设通勤路线上的速度给限制在 50kph 以内。目前 Volvo 的技术已经进步到了可以适应车速、沿线行驶并可处理车流汇集的状况 -- 但这也代表这样的系统还是需要驾驶的全时注意，而官方的最终目标则是让 100 部车辆以全时\"自动驾驶（Autopilot）\"模式下在路上行驶 -- 就让我们期待这次的测试可以让 Volvo 吸取更多经验，带来<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2012/05/29/volvo-driverless-road-train-hits-public-roads-in-spain/\">更有意思的技术</a>展示啰。<br />\n<br />\n经由：<a href=\"http://www.engadget.com/2014/05/06/volvos-self-driving-cars-hit-the-road/\">Engadget</a>、<a href=\"http://www.gizmag.com/volvo-testing-self-driving-cars/31883/pictures#9\">Gizmag</a><br />\n引用来源：<a href=\"https://www.media.volvocars.com/us/en-us/media/pressreleases/145619/volvo-car-groups-first-self-driving-autopilot-cars-test-on-public-roads-around-gothenburg\">Volvo</a><p><h6 style=\"clear: both; padding: 8px 0 0 0; height: 2px; font-size: 1px; border: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"></h6><a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/06/volvos-self-driving-cars-hit-the-road/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent link to this entry\">此文章网址</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/forward/20880987/\" title=\"Send this entry to a friend via email\">转寄此文章</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cn.engadget.com/2014/05/06/volvos-self-driving-cars-hit-the-road/#comments\" title=\"View reader comments on this entry\">回应</a><hr size=\"1\" />", 
